[
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"369530\">@Peter Scholze</span> Here is another thing I'm confused about. At the top of page 60 you explain how to to make the system associated to <code>Mbar r' S</code> admissible. But I think at some point you said that for theorem 9.5 it doesn't actually matter.</p>",
        "id": 230376188,
        "sender_full_name": "Johan Commelin",
        "timestamp": 1615825299
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yes</p>",
        "id": 230376440,
        "sender_full_name": "Peter Scholze",
        "timestamp": 1615825345
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>By taking some suitable restrictions, we can still prove the current statement.</p>",
        "id": 230376459,
        "sender_full_name": "Johan Commelin",
        "timestamp": 1615825349
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>But this affects the constants, doesn't it?</p>",
        "id": 230376486,
        "sender_full_name": "Johan Commelin",
        "timestamp": 1615825356
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Of course it does, but in a controllable way</p>",
        "id": 230376637,
        "sender_full_name": "Peter Scholze",
        "timestamp": 1615825401
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>So it's a tradeoff between the <code>c_i</code> and the <code>k</code> and <code>K</code></p>",
        "id": 230376702,
        "sender_full_name": "Johan Commelin",
        "timestamp": 1615825436
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Which version do you prefer?</p>",
        "id": 230376720,
        "sender_full_name": "Johan Commelin",
        "timestamp": 1615825442
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Hmm, I'm not exactly sure what the question is...</p>",
        "id": 230376911,
        "sender_full_name": "Peter Scholze",
        "timestamp": 1615825518
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think 9.6 needs admissibility, so you want to rescale all maps to make them admissible</p>",
        "id": 230376955,
        "sender_full_name": "Peter Scholze",
        "timestamp": 1615825532
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>or rescale the <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>c</mi><mi>i</mi></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">c_i</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.58056em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">c</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.31166399999999994em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">i</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>'s, sorry</p>",
        "id": 230376995,
        "sender_full_name": "Peter Scholze",
        "timestamp": 1615825554
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Ah, so is the question that of rescaling <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>c</mi><mi>i</mi></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">c_i</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.58056em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">c</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.31166399999999994em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">i</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> vs rescaling the maps?</p>",
        "id": 230377077,
        "sender_full_name": "Peter Scholze",
        "timestamp": 1615825574
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Right, and compose the maps with restriction maps</p>",
        "id": 230377082,
        "sender_full_name": "Johan Commelin",
        "timestamp": 1615825578
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>OK, so in the manuscript I rescaled <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>c</mi><mi>i</mi></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">c_i</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.58056em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">c</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.31166399999999994em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">i</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> (and implicitly composed with restriction maps)</p>",
        "id": 230377187,
        "sender_full_name": "Peter Scholze",
        "timestamp": 1615825619
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Well, I think the question is, for which system would you want us to compute the constants? For the one with rescaled <code>c_i</code> or for the \"original\" system. Or maybe both?</p>",
        "id": 230377216,
        "sender_full_name": "Johan Commelin",
        "timestamp": 1615825629
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>OK, that's hard to say, I think both solutions should be essentially equivalent</p>",
        "id": 230377273,
        "sender_full_name": "Peter Scholze",
        "timestamp": 1615825655
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I'd say it's easier to rescale the <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>c</mi><mi>i</mi></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">c_i</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.58056em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">c</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.31166399999999994em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">i</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> because then one can use variables that are already around</p>",
        "id": 230377326,
        "sender_full_name": "Peter Scholze",
        "timestamp": 1615825678
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I wonder whether we should axiomatize 9.8, and prove 9.5 for all <code>M</code> that satisfy 9.8.</p>",
        "id": 230377573,
        "sender_full_name": "Johan Commelin",
        "timestamp": 1615825782
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Hmm, but that's orthogonal to how we construct the system, so ignore that remark</p>",
        "id": 230377680,
        "sender_full_name": "Johan Commelin",
        "timestamp": 1615825809
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>So, we have these 3 definitions: <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/liquid/index.html#basic_suitable\">https://leanprover-community.github.io/liquid/index.html#basic_suitable</a></p>",
        "id": 230377992,
        "sender_full_name": "Johan Commelin",
        "timestamp": 1615825932
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>And I think we can add one on top, saying that a sequence of <code>c_i</code>s is <code>very_suitable</code>, which depends on Breen--Deligne data + <code>r</code> and <code>r'</code></p>",
        "id": 230378056,
        "sender_full_name": "Johan Commelin",
        "timestamp": 1615825963
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>and then, for <code>very_suitable</code> <code>c_i</code>, we can show that the current definition <code>BD.system</code> spits out an admissible system.</p>",
        "id": 230378187,
        "sender_full_name": "Johan Commelin",
        "timestamp": 1615826032
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The alternative would be to refactor <code>BD.system</code> and rescale the maps...</p>",
        "id": 230378320,
        "sender_full_name": "Johan Commelin",
        "timestamp": 1615826075
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>But I'm not sure that it's easy to abstract over those two approaches, and prove 9.5 for both of them at once</p>",
        "id": 230378349,
        "sender_full_name": "Johan Commelin",
        "timestamp": 1615826092
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>For this rescaling of the <code>c_i</code> we use the assumption <code>r &lt; r'</code>, right? Is this used in any other place? It seems to me that the \"rescale the maps approach\" wouldn't need that assumption.</p>",
        "id": 230378696,
        "sender_full_name": "Johan Commelin",
        "timestamp": 1615826241
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I don't think we need this inequality here</p>",
        "id": 230378727,
        "sender_full_name": "Peter Scholze",
        "timestamp": 1615826263
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Only <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>r</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">r&lt;1</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.5782em;vertical-align:-0.0391em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.02778em;\">r</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">&lt;</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.64444em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">1</span></span></span></span> or something like that</p>",
        "id": 230378778,
        "sender_full_name": "Peter Scholze",
        "timestamp": 1615826283
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The place where it's really used is at the end of the proof of 9.5, there's even a footnote for it! :-)</p>",
        "id": 230378839,
        "sender_full_name": "Peter Scholze",
        "timestamp": 1615826302
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Ooh, yes, I forgot the footnote for a moment</p>",
        "id": 230378866,
        "sender_full_name": "Johan Commelin",
        "timestamp": 1615826319
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>But for the rescaling the <code>c_i</code> approach, you need to know that <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">[</mo><mi>T</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">]</mo><mo>∘</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><msup><mi>T</mi><mrow><mo>−</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><msup><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0em\">∗</mo></msup></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">[T] \\circ(T^{-1})^{*}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">[</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">T</span><span class=\"mclose\">]</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">∘</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.064108em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">T</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.8141079999999999em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">−</span><span class=\"mord mtight\">1</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mclose\"><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.688696em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">∗</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> is norm-nonincreasing, right?</p>",
        "id": 230379064,
        "sender_full_name": "Johan Commelin",
        "timestamp": 1615826407
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>(Dinner time.... see you later.)</p>",
        "id": 230379184,
        "sender_full_name": "Johan Commelin",
        "timestamp": 1615826451
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I don't think so, I only need that restriction from <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>M</mi><mrow><mo>≤</mo><mi>c</mi></mrow></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">M_{\\leq c}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.928509em;vertical-align:-0.24517899999999998em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">M</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.295179em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:-0.10903em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mrel mtight\">≤</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">c</span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.24517899999999998em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> to <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>M</mi><mrow><mo>≤</mo><msup><mi>r</mi><mo lspace=\"0em\" mathvariant=\"normal\" rspace=\"0em\">′</mo></msup><mi>c</mi></mrow></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">M_{\\leq r'c}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.928509em;vertical-align:-0.24517899999999998em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">M</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.32798em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:-0.10903em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mrel mtight\">≤</span><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.02778em;\">r</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.6828285714285715em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.786em;margin-right:0.07142857142857144em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.5em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size3 size1 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">′</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">c</span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.24517899999999998em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> decreases the norm by a factor of <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>r</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">r</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.43056em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.02778em;\">r</span></span></span></span>.</p>",
        "id": 230379306,
